what is data dictionary / ABAP Dictionary (DDIC)
ABAP Dictionary is a central repository in SAP used to define and manage data definitions like tables, data elements, structures, and views.(data dictionary 
is the central hub for all data types in SAP, making sure that every prog works consistently with the same information)
These objects are reusable and globally accessible across ABAP programs and CDS views. 
It ensures data consistency and allows both logical and physical representation of data. 
Objects must be activated to be used, and database tables are physically created upon activation.
Practically, we use SE11 to maintain or create objects in the data dictionary

what CDS View?
CDS views stands for core data services and they're basically a more advanced way to define richer 
data models in sap,especially when you're using a database like HANA.
